    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em data-start=\"1428\" data-end=\"1460\">3rd-level Shadow Lords feature</em></p><p data-start=\"1464\" data-end=\"1683\">Your presence radiates menace. While raging, creatures of your choice within <strong data-start=\"1541\" data-end=\"1552\">10 feet</strong> of you suffer a <strong data-start=\"1569\" data-end=\"1583\">−1 penalty</strong> to attack rolls made against creatures other than you.<br data-start=\"1638\" data-end=\"1641\" />This effect ends if you are incapacitated.</p><p data-start=\"1685\" data-end=\"1723\"><strong data-start=\"1685\" data-end=\"1721\">Auspice Interaction (Choose One)</strong></p><ul data-start=\"1724\" data-end=\"2423\"><li data-start=\"1724\" data-end=\"1876\"><p data-start=\"1726\" data-end=\"1876\"><strong data-start=\"1726\" data-end=\"1739\">Ragabash:</strong> Once per Rage, when a creature misses an attack due to this penalty, you may move up to 10 feet without provoking opportunity attacks.</p></li><li data-start=\"1877\" data-end=\"1999\"><p data-start=\"1879\" data-end=\"1999\"><strong data-start=\"1879\" data-end=\"1891\">Theurge:</strong> While Mantle of Dread is active, you gain advantage on saving throws against being charmed or frightened.</p></li><li data-start=\"2000\" data-end=\"2158\"><p data-start=\"2002\" data-end=\"2158\"><strong data-start=\"2002\" data-end=\"2015\">Philodox:</strong> Once per Rage, when a creature affected by Mantle of Dread targets an ally, you may use your reaction to impose disadvantage on that attack.</p></li><li data-start=\"2159\" data-end=\"2282\"><p data-start=\"2161\" data-end=\"2282\"><strong data-start=\"2161\" data-end=\"2174\">Galliard:</strong> When Mantle of Dread first activates, one ally within 30 feet gains advantage on their next saving throw.</p></li><li data-start=\"2283\" data-end=\"2423\"><p data-start=\"2285\" data-end=\"2423\"><strong data-start=\"2285\" data-end=\"2296\">Ahroun:</strong> Once per turn, when you hit a creature affected by Mantle of Dread, you may deal extra damage equal to your proficiency bonus.</p></li></ul>",
